Sentencas: The effects of sintering temperatures on the performances and durabilities of conventional nickel-yttria-stabilized zirconia composite solid oxide fuel cell anodes were investigated.
Titulo: Quantitative Study on the Correlation Between Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Ni-YSZ Composite Anode Performance and Sintering Temperature Based on Three-dimensional Reconstruction

Sentencas: The anode microstructures after reduction and 100 hours operation were quantitatively analyzed by three-dimensional reconstruction based on focused ion beam-scanning electron microscopy technique.
Titulo: Quantitative Study on the Correlation Between Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Ni-YSZ Composite Anode Performance and Sintering Temperature Based on Three-dimensional Reconstruction

Sentencas: Percolation of nickel, yttria-stabilized zirconia and pore phases and three phase boundary densities were quantitatively calculated.
Titulo: Quantitative Study on the Correlation Between Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Ni-YSZ Composite Anode Performance and Sintering Temperature Based on Three-dimensional Reconstruction

Sentencas: The anode sintered at 1450 degrees C has been found to show the minimum ohmic resistance and polarization resistance.
Titulo: Quantitative Study on the Correlation Between Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Ni-YSZ Composite Anode Performance and Sintering Temperature Based on Three-dimensional Reconstruction

Sentencas: The differences of ohmic resistances between the anodes can be quantitatively explained by the difference of active three phase boundary density.
Titulo: Quantitative Study on the Correlation Between Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Ni-YSZ Composite Anode Performance and Sintering Temperature Based on Three-dimensional Reconstruction

Sentencas: Besides, the anode sintered at 1450 degrees C could operate without large-scale channel cracks which may cause damage and relatively fast degradation.
Titulo: Quantitative Study on the Correlation Between Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Ni-YSZ Composite Anode Performance and Sintering Temperature Based on Three-dimensional Reconstruction

Sentencas: The lowest degradation rate of anode sintered at 1450 degrees C is attributed to the strengthened YSZ network for maintaining Ni phase percolation compared to the other two sintering temperatures.
Titulo: Quantitative Study on the Correlation Between Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Ni-YSZ Composite Anode Performance and Sintering Temperature Based on Three-dimensional Reconstruction
